<title>VBJ Editor's Choice</title>
</head>


<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
					VLINK="#E8171A"
					ALINK="#E8171A">

<body>


<center><img src="graphics/edchoice.gif" alt="Editor's Choice"></center><br><br><br>

<font size=+1>
<blockquote>Type in "Vietnam" at your search engine and you're likely to be flooded with thousands of sites.<p>

Which ones are really worth visiting? Every month the editors at <b>T<small>HE</small> V<small>IETNAM</small> B<small>USINESS</small> J<small>OURNAL</small></b> will give you more than just a list. We'll link you to Vietnam-related sites which are especially useful, up-to-date, unique, or just plain enjoyable.<p>

This month, we've added five new sites sites including two important regional sites: the International Monetary Fund and the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation group.<p>

If your interest is business or culture in Vietnam, Indochina, or Southeast Asia, remember to bookmark The VBJ's home page for links to the latest relevant, informative and colorful web sites. We also welcome your suggestions for this listing. Please send an e-mail message to <a href="mailto:editor'schoice@viam.com">editor'schoice@viam.com</a>.<p>

To visit a site, click on the image below.</blockquote></font><br><br>





<tt><center>



<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.jaring.my:80/at-asia/camb_at_asia/camb_times/ct_list.html"><img src="graphics/websites/cambodiatimes.gif" border=0 alt="Cambodia Times"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Cambodia Times</font><p>
<tt> The first English-language daily<br>to be printed in Phnom Penh since the civil war.<br>Updates on Cambodia's shifting political, economic, and military scenes.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.jaring.my:80/at-asia/camb_at_asia/camb_times/ct_list.html">http://www.jaring.my:80/at-asia/camb_at_asia/camb_times/ct_list.html</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.imf.org"><img src="graphics/websites/imf.gif" border=0 alt="IMF"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>International Monetary Fund (IMF)</font><p>
<tt>A newly-created website for the multilateral-aid agency.<br>Provides macroeconomic outlook and aid programs for Vietnam<br>and other nations of Southeast Asia.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.imf.org">http://www.imf.org</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.apecsec.org.sg/apecnet.html"><img src="graphics/websites/apec.gif" border=0 alt="APEC"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC)</font><p>
<tt>Information on the  group.<br>Includes updates on Vietnam's bid to enter APEC<br>and transcripts of latest APEC meeting at Subic Bay.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.apecsec.org.sg/apecnet.html">http://www.apecsec.org.sg/apecnet.html</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.pbs.org/pov/stories/vietnam/about.html"><img src="graphics/websites/vstories.jpg" border=0 alt="Stories of the Vietnam Memorial"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Stories of the Vietnam Memorial</font><p>
<tt>America's Public Broadcasting Service (PBS)<br>site dedicated to the Vietnam Veterans Memorial<br>designed by Maya Lin.<br>Vietnam Veterans and visitors to the Memorial share their reflections.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.pbs.org/pov/stories/vietnam/about.html">http://www.pbs.org/pov/stories/vietnam/about.html</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.well.com/www/gdisf/dvhome.html"><img src="graphics/websites/dv.gif" border=0 alt="Destination Vietnam"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Destination Vietnam</font><p>
<tt>Travel magazine specializing in Vietnamese art and artists.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.well.com/www/gdisf/dvhome.html">http://www.well.com/www/gdisf/dvhome.html</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/~vern/vninfo/vcci.htm"><img src="graphics/websites/vcci.gif" border=0 alt="VCCI"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Vietnam Chamber of Commerce and Industry (VCCI)</font><p>
<tt>Introduction to the VCCI - a good first stop<br>for investors new to Vietnam.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/~vern/vninfo/vcci.htm">http://coombs.anu.edu.au/~vern/vninfo/vcci.htm</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.rajgallery.com/ste/ste_1.html"><img src="graphics/websites/steinhauer.gif" border=0 alt="Peter Steinhauer Photography"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Peter Steinhauer Photography</font><p>
<tt>Black and white portraits and landscapes of Vietnam.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.rajgallery.com/ste/ste_1.html">http://www.rajgallery.com/ste/ste_1.html</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.feer.com"><img src="graphics/websites/feer.gif" border=0 alt="Far Eastern Economic Review"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Far Eastern Economic Review Interactive Edition</font><p>
<tt>The interactive edition of the Far Eastern Economic Review.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.feer.com">http://www.feer.com</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.tripprep.com"><img src="graphics/websites/health.gif" border=0 alt="Travel Health Online"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Travel Health Online</font><p>
<tt>Shoreland's guide to travel health and safety. Recommended vaccinations, health precautions<br>and US State Department travel advisories.<br>Visit this site at<br><a href="http://www.tripprep.com">http://www.tripprep.com</a>.<p><br><br>

<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVLPages/VietPages/WWWVL-Vietnam.html"><img src="graphics/websites/anuwwwvl.gif" border=0 alt="ANU's WWW-VL on Vietnam"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>ANU's W3 Virtual Library on Vietnam</font><p>
<tt>An enormous collection of Vietnam-related links -- over 1000 -- compiled<br>by Vern Weitzel at the Coombs Computing Unit,<br>Research Schools of Social Sciences &amp; Pacific and Asian Studies<br>at the Australian National University.  Visit this site at<br><a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVLPages/VietPages/WWWVL-Vietnam.html">http://coombs.anu.edu.au/WWWVLPages/VietPages/WWWVL-Vietnam.html</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://vweb.net/vietweb/"><img src="graphics/websites/vietweb.gif" border=0 alt="Viet Web"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Viet Web</font><p>
<tt>Comprehensive Vietnamese-culture site presenting Vietnamese<br>poetry, music, literature and arts. Connections to the<br>expatriate Vietnamese community in the US and throughout the world.<br>Primarily a Vietnamese-language site at <a href="http://vweb.net/vietweb/">http://vweb.net/vietweb</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.webcom.com/~hcgvn/software/software.html"><img src="graphics/websites/software.gif" border=0 alt="Vietnamese Software Fonts"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>VPS Vietnamese Fonts</font><p>
<tt>Download the popular Vietnamese-language software provided by the Vietnamese<br>Professionals Society at <a href="http://www.webcom.com/~hcgvn/software/software.html">http://www.webcom.com/~hcgvn/software/software.html</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://sunsite.nus.sg/ais/ais-info.html"><img src="graphics/websites/sunsite.gif" border=0 alt="ASEAN Server Database"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>ASEAN Internet Search</font><p>
<tt>ASEAN information search engine<br>hosted by Singapore National University at<br><a href="http://sunsite.nus.sg/ais/ais-info.html">http://sunsite.nus.sg/ais/ais-info.html</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.saigon.com"><img src="graphics/websites/VietGATE.gif" border=0 alt="VietGATE"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>VietGATE</font><p>
<tt>VietGATE is the gateway to the on-line Vietnamese community.<br>The site includes Vietnamese culture, media, databases<br>and connections to people interested in Vietnam at<br><a href="http://www.saigon.com">http://www.saigon.com</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.ita.doc.gov/itahome.htm"><img src="graphics/websites/ITA.gif" border=0 alt="ITA"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>International Trade Administration</font><p>
<tt>US Commerce Department's ITA site. Information on<br>exporting to Vietnam, ASEAN, and Big Emerging Markets (BEMs).<br>Link to Asia Business Center at Department of Commerce.<br>Visit this site at <a href="http://www.ita.doc.gov/itahome.htm">http://www.ita.doc.gov/itahome.htm</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/~vern/space/space2.html"><img src="graphics/websites/space.gif" border=0 alt="Vietnam From Space"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Vietnam From Space</font><p>
<tt>Satellite images of different regions in Vietnam, geographical information,<br>and comments from Vietnamese astronaut Pham Tuan, who orbited<br>the earth on the Soyuz 37 spacecraft in July 1980.<br>Getting frustrated with day-to-day business in Vietnam?<br>Take a look at the big picture at <a href="http://coombs.anu.edu.au/~vern/space/space2.html">http://coombs.anu.edu.au/~vern/space/space2.html</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width =260><p>
<a href="http://amalthea.sjsu.edu/depts/litart/tobrien1.html"><img src="graphics/websites/tophoto.gif" border=0 alt="Tim O'Brien Photo"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>The Vietnam In Me</font><p>
<tt>Essay by acclaimed author and Vietnam-veteran Tim O'Brien,<br>originally published in <i>The New York Times Magazine</i>.<br>A haunting look at one Veteran's return to Vietnam in 1994.<br>Part of the "Modern Masters" authors series at <a href="http://amalthea.sjsu.edu/depts/litart/tobrien1.html">http://amalthea.sjsu.edu/depts/litart/tobrien1.html</a>. Also recommended:<br>Tim O'Brien's short story "The Things They Carried."<p><br><br>


<no shade width=260><p>
<a href="http://jica.ific.or.jp/Index.html"><img src="graphics/websites/jica.gif" border=0 alt="JICA/IFIC"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Japan International Cooperation Agency and Institute for International Cooperation</font><p>
<tt>Lending agency from the world's largest donor of financial aid<br>to Vietnam -- Japan. Information about Japanese-funded<br>infrastructure projects up for tender<br>and macroeconomic analysis of Vietnam at <a href="http://jica.ific.or.jp/Index.html">http://jica.ific.or.jp/Index.html</a>.<p><br><br>


<hr noshade width=260><p>
<a href="http://www.saigon.com/~vacets/It2k/index.html"><img src="graphics/websites/itinviet.gif" border=0 alt="IT In Vietnam"></a><p>
</tt><font color=225EC0 size=+2>Electronic and Information Technology In Vietnam</font><p>
<tt>A 1994 UN-sponsored report presented to Vietnam's Ministry of Science,<br>Technology and the Environment that helped serve as<br>the foundation for Vietnam's IT2000 plan<br>at <a href="http://www.saigon.com/~vacets/It2k/index.html">http://www.saigon.com/~vacets/It2k/index.html</a>.<p><br><br>

</tt></font>
</center>


