<a href="#top">Return to Top of Page</a>
<p><br><br>

<a name="comod">
<table border=2>
<caption><b>COMMODITIES FILE<sup>1</sup></b></caption>

<th>Commodity<th>Price<th>Outlook
<tr><tr><tr>

<tr><td align=top><b>Rice</b> (Cash offers, FOB)<td align=center align=top><b>25% Brokens</b>: $240-$245/ton<td align=left><b>Outlook</b>: End-of-season trading light. Diminishing stocks keeping prices stable above $240/ton, up from $200-$205/ton in early October. Exports projected to reach 3.2 million tons in 1996. Quota set for 3.0 million tons in 1997.

<tr><td align=top><b>Coffee</b> (Cash offers, FOB)<td align=center align=top><b>Grade 2 Robusta</b>:<br> $1,000/ton for 1st quarter delivery.<td align=left><b>Outlook</b>: Heavy rains over past two months delayed drying and sales during peak season in October/ November. Some concerns about mold/moisture content of some shipments. Demand for grade 2 robusta has remained slow after Indonesia's peak-season, with some shipments at $930/ton. 

<tr><td align=top><b>Pepper</b> (Cash offers, FOB)<td align=center align=top><b>(Fair-Average Quality)</b>:<br> $2,300-$2,400/ton for February-March shipment.<td align=left><b>Outlook</b>: 1997 crop expected in February. Preliminary estimates put crop at 16,000-18,000 tons.


<tr><tr><tr>
<td colspan=3><font size=-1><sup>1</sup> Tons are metric tons.</font>


</table><br>
